        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 12:53AM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 1252 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 14 miles northeast of Long Point to near Carta
Valley to 17 miles north of Alamo Village. Movement was north at 60
mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rocksprings, Loma Alta, Us-377 Near The Kimble-
Edwards County Line, Devil's Sinkhole State Natural Area, Vinegarone,
Carta Valley, Us-277 Near The Sutton-
Edwards County Line, Kickapoo Cavern State Park, and Devils River
State Nat Area Del Norte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
